title: Flytippers completely block country lane with rubbish | Daily Mail Online
text: comments Flytippers dumped a huge pile of stinking rubbish down a country lane, blocking access to vehicles. The mass of steaming waste, including food and dirty nappies, appeared in the village of Yoxall, Staffordshire, on Friday afternoon. Furious villagers think the rubbish might have been left by a lorry that dumped its load after realising it had driven down a dead end. He said: 'It is absolutely disgusting. I have never seen anything like it in my life. 'It stinks to high heaven. There's all sorts in there - food, dirty nappies - I dread to think what else.
